com.worldpay.innovation.wpwithin

Interface WPWithinWrapper

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    WPWithinWrapperImpl

    public interface WPWithinWrapper
    Worldpay Within Java Wrapper Interface to be coding against and will give you access to the underlying Golang SDK, via RPC calls made by Thrift.
    Author:
    worldpay

      • initConsumer

        void initConsumer(String scheme,
                  String hostname,
                  Integer port,
                  String urlPrefix,
                  String serverId,
                  WWHCECard hceCard,
                  Map<String,String> pspConfig)
           throws WPWithinGeneralException
        This initiates the device as a consumer, which enables it to find services, negotiate prices, make payments and receive services.
        Parameters:
        scheme - This should be 'http://' or 'https://'
        hostname - This will be host name, find this from the service messages
        port - This will be the port for the device, find this from the service message
        urlPrefix - This will be the urlPrefix for which the restful interface of the producer is located at
        serverId - This is the unique Id of the server of the producer, provided by the service message
        hceCard - This is the payment credentials to configure the consumer with, which it will use to make payments
        pspConfig - represent configuration for PSP integration i.e. online.worldpay.com or SecureNet
        Throws:
        WPWithinGeneralException

      • selectService

        WWTotalPriceResponse selectService(Integer serviceId,
                                   Integer numberOfUnits,
                                   Integer priceId)
                            throws WPWithinGeneralException
        Selection of a service is performed by the consumer, providing details of the service, the amount and at what price point it wants to purchase the service.
        Parameters:
        serviceId - The id of the service to be purchased
        numberOfUnits - The number of units to purchase
        priceId - The PriceId of the price that is to be chosen
        Returns:
        The TotalPriceResponse object is provided back which details how much the service will cost based on the requested service details.
        Throws:
        WPWithinGeneralException

      • makePayment

        WWPaymentResponse makePayment(WWTotalPriceResponse request)
                       throws WPWithinGeneralException
        This allows the consumer to request a payment be made at the producer device, by providing the total price response object as the request. The producer will then make the payment (or attempt to) and send back a Payment Response detailing whether it was successful or not.
        Parameters:
        request - The TotalPriceResponse object detailing the agreement of the service that will be purchased.
        Returns:
        Returns the Payment Response as to whether it was successful or not
        Throws:
        WPWithinGeneralException

      • beginServiceDelivery

        WWServiceDeliveryToken beginServiceDelivery(int serviceId,
                                            WWServiceDeliveryToken serviceDeliveryToken,
                                            Integer unitsToSupply)
                                     throws WPWithinGeneralException
        This begins the service delivery, and is requested by the consumer, and will proceed as long as the correct information is provided to the producer. If the correct credentials are passed through, then the producer will start releasing the service known as a 'trusted trigger'
        Parameters:
        serviceId - Id of service being delivered service
        serviceDeliveryToken - The secure token that details the usage of the service, and the producer will know if it has been paid for and is still valid
        unitsToSupply - This is how many units of service being requested at this time.
        Throws:
        WPWithinGeneralException

      • endServiceDelivery

        WWServiceDeliveryToken endServiceDelivery(int serviceID,
                                          WWServiceDeliveryToken serviceDeliveryToken,
                                          Integer unitsReceived)
                                   throws WPWithinGeneralException
        This ends the service delivery, a request initiated by the consumer.
        Parameters:
        serviceID - Id of service being delivered
        serviceDeliveryToken - The secure token that details the usage of the service
        unitsReceived - The number of units received - to confirm that this is consistent with what the produce understands
        Throws:
        WPWithinGeneralException
